## 6. Vapi/Retell Call UI Conventions (clone target)

**Active call card:**
- Avatar circle (initials or phone icon) with 3-ring pulsing animation in amber (#F59E0B) at 1.5s intervals
- Waveform: 5 vertical bars (heights: 8px, 20px, 36px, 20px, 8px baseline), CSS `@keyframes wave` animation — each bar cycles independently with 0.1s stagger
- Call timer: monospace font (DM Mono), counts up from 00:00, positioned top-right of card

**Status pill progression:**
```
CONNECTING (gray dot) → ACTIVE (green dot, pulse) → ON HOLD (amber) → TRANSFERRING (blue spin) → ENDED (slate)
```

**Transcript bubbles:**
- AI (left-aligned): teal bg (#0D9488), white text, rounded 16px, max-w 75%, DM Mono font 13px
- Caller (right-aligned): white bg, slate-800 text, border 1px teal-100, same rounding
- New messages slide in from bottom with 200ms ease-out
- Timestamp in slate-400 12px below each bubble

**Intent badge:** Appears after first AI response, floats over call card:
```
BOOK APPT (teal) | FAQ (emerald) | ESCALATE (red, animated shake) | UNCLEAR (amber)
```

**Confidence meter:**
- Horizontal bar, full width of call card, height 6px
- Gradient: ≥0.70 emerald-500 → 0.45-0.70 amber-500 → <0.45 red-500 (triggers auto-escalate)
- Numeric label: "Confidence: 82%" in DM Mono 11px slate-500, right-aligned

**Automation pipeline viz (InboundCall.jsx embedded):**
Horizontal SVG flow, nodes light up teal as call progresses:
```
[Greeting] → [Intent Detect] → [Booking|FAQ|Escalate] → [Webhook Trigger] → [SMS Confirm]
```
Node: 36px circle + label below, connected by dashed line. Active node = solid teal fill + drop shadow.

